Interface RDKitObjectCleaner

    public interface RDKitObjectCleaner
    This interface defines methods to register RDKit objects, which are subject of later cleanup.
    Author:
    Manuel Schwarze

    • Method Detail

      • createUniqueCleanupWaveId

        long createUniqueCleanupWaveId()
        Creates a new wave id. This id must be unique in the context of the overall runtime of the Java VM, at least in the context of the same class loader and memory area.
        Returns:
        Unique wave id.

      • markForCleanup

        <T> T markForCleanup(T rdkitObject)
        Registers an RDKit based object, which must have a delete() method implemented for freeing up resources later. The cleanup will happen for all registered objects when the method cleanupMarkedObjects() is called.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Any class that implements a delete() method to be called to free up resources.
        Parameters:
        rdkitObject - An RDKit related object that should free resources when not used anymore. Can be null.
        Returns:
        The same object that was passed in. Null, if null was passed in.
        See Also:
        #markForCleanup(Object, int)

      • markForCleanup

        <T> T markForCleanup(T rdkitObject,
                     long wave)
        Registers an RDKit based object that is used within a certain block (wave). $ This object must have a delete() method implemented for freeing up resources later. The cleanup will happen for all registered objects when the method #cleanupMarkedObjects(int) is called with the same wave.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Any class that implements a delete() method to be called to free up resources.
        Parameters:
        rdkitObject - An RDKit related object that should free resources when not used anymore. Can be null.
        wave - A number that identifies objects registered for a certain "wave".
        Returns:
        The same object that was passed in. Null, if null was passed in.
        See Also:
        markForCleanup(Object)

      • cleanupMarkedObjects

        void cleanupMarkedObjects()
        Frees resources for all objects that have been registered prior to this last call using the method cleanupMarkedObjects().

      • cleanupMarkedObjects

        void cleanupMarkedObjects(long wave)
        Frees resources for all objects that have been registered prior to this last call for a certain wave using the method #cleanupMarkedObjects(int).
        Parameters:
        wave - A number that identifies objects registered for a certain "wave".
